(fifthQuint)A Study of the Feasibility of Prehospital Remote Ischemic Conditioning.

 This single-arm, open-label pilot study will evaluate the feasibility of delivering remote ischemic conditioning (RIC) by emergency medical services (EMS) in the prehospital setting.

 Eligible patients will be at least 18 years of age, and require ground ambulance transport to the hospital.

 Patients suspected of ST-elevation myocardial infarction (STEMI) based on the prehospital electrocardiogram and thus requiring urgent intervention in the cardiac catheterization lab will be excluded.

 All subjects will undergo the standard RIC procedure (i.

e.

, up to four cycles of alternating 5-min inflation and 5-min deflation) with the autoRIC(R) device (CellAegis Devices, Inc.

