 The automated procedure will be initiated by paramedics during ambulance transport, and the RIC cycles will continue through emergency department (ED) arrival and stay for a total of 40 minutes.

 The primary objective of this pilot study is to examine the duration of RIC administered in patients having the procedure initiated in the prehospital setting.

 The investigators hypothesize four cycles of RIC will be completed in at least 80% of patients having the procedure initiated.

 Secondary objectives are to assess enrollment rates and protocol implementation; paramedic acceptability of protocol; and patient tolerability of RIC.

